      <p>For rural health organizations not yet deep in the RHTP weeds, the March 30 call is a low-barrier entry point. The state is expected to outline the scoring rubric for the current workforce grants, preview subsequent grant windows — access expansion, telehealth, healthy lifestyles, and technology — and field questions from prospective applicants.</p>
