      </div>

      <p>The new Medicaid provisions — work requirements, semiannual eligibility check-ins, and coverage exemptions — were embedded in last summer's federal budget reconciliation package. In North Dakota, roughly 23,000 Medicaid expansion enrollees will be subject to the new rules, out of more than 108,000 total recipients statewide.</p>

